  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The validation requirement mandates a controlled-experiment verification method; the supporting validation activity was conducted as an observational study of clinical pump returns and in-service hemolysis measurements. The narrative presents the observational data as a rigorous empirical complement to the CFD predictions, emphasizing the breadth of the dataset (n=312 pump-hours across 47 patients) and the fidelity of the hemolysis index measurements. However, the structured activityType field records the activity as 'observational-study', which does not satisfy the 'controlled-experiment' requirement encoded in the binding Requirement node. The inference link from evidence to credibility claim is therefore broken under W-AR-03.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-verification-req-01",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-credibility-claim-01",
